The `name` attribute in both `@RequestMapping` and `@GetMapping` just configure the name of the mapping. It is nothing related to the API path. You should use `path` or `value` instead : 

``` java
@RestController
@RequestMapping(&quot;/api/v1&quot;)
public class ModelMockerController {

    @GetMapping(&quot;/mock&quot;)
    public String hello(){
        return &quot;Hello&quot;;
    }
}

```

or 

``` java
@RestController
@RequestMapping(path = &quot;/api/v1&quot;)
public class ModelMockerController {

    @GetMapping(path = &quot;/mock&quot;)
    public String hello(){
        return &quot;Hello&quot;;
    }
}

```

