Your code tries to read `database.child(&quot;User&quot;).child(firebaseUser.getUid())`, but the key under the `User` node is not a UID. That explains why the code can&#39;t find the data.

If you want to be able to look up the user by their UID, you should first store the data under the UID of the user. It look like currently you do something like:

```
ref.child(&quot;User&quot;).push().setValue(userdata);
```

The `push()` call in here creates the `-NP` key. To store the data under the user&#39;s UID, you&#39;ll want to do:

```
String uid = FirebaseAuth.getInstance().getCurrentUser().getUid();

ref.child(&quot;User&quot;).child(uid).setValue(userdata);
```

